  "prompt": "Do snakes eat penguins?",
  "response": "No, snakes do not typically eat penguins. Snakes and penguins do not usually inhabit the same environments. Penguins are primarily found in colder regions like Antarctica and some other southern hemisphere locations, whereas snakes are more commonly found in warmer climates and diverse habitats ranging from forests and deserts to wetlands. Therefore, their paths rarely cross, making it unlikely for snakes to prey on penguins.",
